<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - OIL PICKUP TUBE INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OIL PICKUP TUBE INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the oil pickup tube assembly as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Wipe oil from the front cover inlet tube gasket surface.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using a new gasket, remove the release paper and apply the gasket to the front
                        cover.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Be sure the gasket is properly aligned before applying it to the front cover. Once
                                applied, the gasket will stick to the front cover. An out of position gasket can cause
                                low or no oil pressure and bearing damage.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosely install the two mounting bolts and washers through the front cover and
                        fasten the oil pickup tube. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150784">7.84</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef4150782" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg12197" filename="../figcg1/cg12197.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.82. Trim Excess Front Cover Gasket.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4150783" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11621" filename="../figcg1/cg11621.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.83. Trim Excess Flywheel Housing Gasket.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4150784" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11623" filename="../figcg1/cg11623.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.84. Fasten Oil Pickup Tube.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Align the pickup tube bracket with the crankcase mounting pad and loosely install
                        the mounting bolt with the lock washer and hardened washer. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e415_160.xml" xrefid="ef4150785">7.85</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        . Once aligned, tighten the front bolts alternately until secured (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150784">7.84</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ). Once the oil pick-up tube to front cover bolts are tightened, secure the pickup tube bracket
                        (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e415_160.xml" xrefid="ef4150785">7.85</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ). (Rear sump tube shown).
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
